<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Amorous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Amorous,</orth> 1) pertaining to love: <cit><quote>his a. spoil,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lc 154" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 154</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my a. tale,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.327" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 327</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>your a. token,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.68" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 68</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>fetter'd in a. chains,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 15</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. rites,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 8</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>their a. sojourn,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 48</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his a. works,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 213</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) fond, in love: <cit><quote>our fine musician groweth a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 1, 63</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.195" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 195</bibl>. <cit><quote>a. Phillida,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 68</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.8.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 8, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 149</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.5.72" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 5, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 5, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 1, 33</bibl>. <cit><quote>unloose his a. fold,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.223" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 223</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>bent of a. view,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.282" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 282</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>Phoebus' a. pinches,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.5.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 5, 28</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to court an a. lookingglass,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 15</bibl></cit>, i. e. a looking-glass which reflects a face fond of itself.
<lb />Followed by <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>a. of their strokes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 202</bibl></cit>. by <emph>on</emph>: <cit><quote>a. on Hero,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 161</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>